rates on a continuum of spatial and temporal scales in such a way that the variability exhibits scaling relationships                                                     Climatologically relevant imprints of scaling include long‐range dependence and non‐Gaussian fluctuations                                                     Scaling has implications for trend detection, climate sensitivity, and predictability},
